cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.IT, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the problem of finding minimal automata for different subregular language families. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the complexity of constructing minimal automata for different language families. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper deals with the logical properties of regular languages and automata. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the concept of magic numbers and their existence in different language families. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of constructing minimal automata for different language families.
